      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4>Activity</h4>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-desmos-gc\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\"></div>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <ol type=\"a\">\n      <li>Use the graphing tool&nbsp; above or technology outside the course, on the same coordinate grid, graph the following linear functions. Use a different color for each: </li>\n    </ol>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\\(\n        f(x)=x+4\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x+2\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x-2\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x-4\\) </li>\n    </ul>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p> Then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to check your work. </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n  <p>Compare your graph to the one below:</p>\n  <p><img alt=\"This graph shows six versions of the function, f of x = x, on an x, y coordinate plane. The x-axis runs from negative 8 to 8, and the y axis runs negative 8 to 8. There are five lines parallel to each other. The first line extends from the bottom left quadrant to the upper right quadrant on the coordinate plane. This line shows f of x = x plus 4 which has a slope of 1 and a y-intercept at 4. The next line also extends from the bottom left quadrant to the upper right quadrant and shows f of x = x plus 2 which has a slope of 1 and a y-intercept at 2. The next and middle line, extends from the lower left quadrant, through the center of the graph at point (0, 0) to the upper right quadrant and shows f of x = x. The next line extends from the lower left quadrant, through the lower right quadrant to the upper right quadrant. This line shows f of x = x minus 2 which has a slope of 1 and a y-intercept at -2. The last line extends from the lower left quadrant, through the lower right quadrant to the upper right quadrant.This line shows f of x = x minus 4 which has a slope of 1 and a y-intercept at -4.\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/0120bf1497785e3d10342ceca2ddf50bf6a0d285\"></p>\n</div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol start=\"2\">\n      <li>What is the slope of each line?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>1</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset\" data-button-text=\"Check\" data-fire-learning-opportunity-event=\"eventnameY\" data-fire-success-event=\"eventnameX\" data-retry-limit=\"3\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <!--Q3-->\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-problem\" data-problem-type=\"dropdown\" data-solution=\"Shift up 2\" data-solution-options='[\"Shift up 2\", \"Shift down 2\", \"Shift right 2\", \"Shift left 2\"]'>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-problem-content\">\n      <ol start=\"3\">\n        <li>How can the parent function, \\(f(x)=x\\), be shifted to overlap \\(f(x)=x+2\\)?</li>\n      </ol>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-correct-response\">\n      <p>Correct! </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-encourage-response\">\n      <p>Try again. </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-attempts-exhausted-response\">\n      <p>The correct answer is Shift up 2. You seem to be stuck. Who can you ask for help?</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <!--END QUESTION.-->\n  <!--Q4-->\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-problem\" data-problem-type=\"dropdown\" data-solution=\"Shift down 4\" data-solution-options='[\"Shift up 4\", \"Shift down 4\", \"Shift right 4\", \"Shift left 4\"]'>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-problem-content\">\n      <ol start=\"4\">\n        <li>How can the parent function, \\(f(x)=x\\), be shifted to overlap \\(f(x)=x-4\\)?</li>\n      </ol>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-correct-response\">\n      <p>Correct! </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-encourage-response\">\n      <p>Try again. </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-attempts-exhausted-response\">\n      <p>The correct answer is Shift down 4. You seem to be stuck. Who can you ask for help?</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <!--END QUESTION.-->\n  <!--Do not edit below line.-->\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-correct-response\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-pset-encourage-response\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <ol start=\"5\">\n      <li></li>\n    </ol>\n    <ul>\n      <li>\\(\n        f(x)=x+4\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x+2\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x-2\\) </li>\n      <li> \\(f(x)=x-4\\) </li>\n    </ul>\n    <p>What changed with these functions? How did this change their graphs?</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p>Write down your answer, then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to check your work. </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n  <p>Compare your answers:</p>\n  <p>The constant added to or subtracted from x changed. When a number was added to x, it shifted the line up that many units. When a number was subtracted from x, it shifted the line down that many units.. </p>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>In \\(f(x)=mx+b\\), the \\(b\\) acts as the <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">vertical shift</span>. This is a type of <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">transformation</span> to the graph of \\(f(x)=x\\). The vertical shift &ldquo;transforms&rdquo; the parent function into another function.</p>"
    }
  ]
}